{
  "texts": [
    "Table 4 presents statistics of the representative datasets.",
    "TUDatasets is a widely adopted graph machine learning benchmark dataset collection, which contains graph data in multiple fields, such as bioinformatics, chemical molecular structure, and social networks.",
    "Datasets such as PROTEINS (Dobson and Doig 2003; Borgwardt et al. 2005), ENZYMES (Borgwardt et al. 2005; Schomburg et al. 2004), and DD (Dobson and Doig 2003; Shervashidze et al. 2011) provide rich biomolecular network data, such as protein interaction networks and structural data of enzymes.",
    "These data sets provide a valuable resource for researchers to explore the functions and interaction patterns of biomolecules.",
    "Datasets such as MUTAG (Debnath et al. 1991), NCI1 (Wale et al. 2008), NCI109 (Wale et al. 2008), Mutagenicity (Kazius et al. 2005), and FRANKENSTEIN (Orsini et al. 2015) mainly focus on chemical molecular structure graphs, providing important benchmarks for evaluating the performance of graph neural networks in fields such as molecular property prediction and drug discovery."
  ]
}